OL,3,CZoo gets new capybara as search for
OL,4,Cmissing Samba continues
OL,6,FMarwell Zoo has welcomed the arrival
OL,7,Fof a seven-year-old capybara as search
OL,8,Fefforts continue for another that
OL,9,Fescaped earlier this year.
OL,11,FThe zoo said it was "delighted" to
OL,12,Fbegin caring for the animal, a male
OL,13,Fnamed Ripple, after his transfer from
OL,14,FBlackpool Zoo.
OL,16,FRipple is gradually being introduced
OL,17,Fto the zoo's resident female, Tango -
OL,18,Fwho is the sister of Samba, the
OL,19,Fcapybara whose escape back in March
OL,20,Fled to a public appeal for her safe
OL,21,Freturn.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/3
